  "title": "IT Sales Manager | Networking IoT and Telecomm",
  "description": "<ul><li><p><strong>Role: Head of Sales / Sales Manager</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Working Days: Monday to Friday (5 days per week)</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Working Hours: 9:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Work Location: Genting Lane [ Between Mattar / Potong Pasir MRT ]</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Starting Salary: SGD 6,500 – SGD 9,500 + Bonus</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>Summary:</strong></p><ul><li><p>MNC Company Headquarter with more than 10 Operations Office in Europe, Asia, North & South America.</p></li><li><p><em><strong>Company is specialist in Industrial IoT Routers & Gateways, providing 4G / 5G routers, gateways, Wi-Fi, and Ethernet switches to businesses.</strong></em></p></li><li><p>The Head of Sales is responsible to led the networking solutions business unit to develop manufactures industrial and enterprise connectivity equipment, primarily routers, switches, gateways and modems.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><p>A minimum of <strong>5 years</strong> of work experience in<strong> B2B sales in IT or Networking Solutions</strong></p></li><li><p>At least <strong>2 years of leadership</strong> and managerial experience, showcasing a proud track record of results</p></li><li><p>Market knowledge: <strong>Experience in the IoT and Telecommunication industries.</strong></p></li></ol><p><strong>Job Scopes:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead, mentor, and cultivate a high-performing sales team to achieve excellence.</p></li><li><p>Strategically manage the team, ensuring the realization of 100% of the sales plan through effective leadership and motivation.</p></li><li><p>Design and execute comprehensive training programs, providing ongoing support to the sales team to enhance their skills and capabilities.</p></li><li><p>Oversee and maintain the accuracy of internal systems, ensuring that team members consistently input information correctly.</p></li><li><p>Play a pivotal role in market research, identifying potential markets and cultivating growth opportunities for the team.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate closely with the Regional Sales Director, contributing your leadership expertise to accomplish assigned tasks and further the success of the sales department.</p></li></ul><p><br /><br /></p><p>#SCR-carson-cheong</p><p>⭕ Cheong Kar Chun ⭕ Team Manager ⭕ R1980386</p><p>⭕ The Supreme HR Advisory ⭕ 14C7279</p>",
